the file ml.py is the project file to conduct both the analysis and the machine learning procedure.
txt_sentoken and sub directories are the test files and processed files
requirements.txt is the file of the packages used.

to build
download and extract the project
navigate to the project directory
create a new virtual env using the command: py -m venv env or python3 -m venv env
Install the required packages outlined in requirements.txt
type python ml.py <-a> <-f n>\\where -a will only conduct the analysis\\ -f n will run with n folds

Testing was done on small scall project via manual calculations of the f values and some trust that the packages in scikit-learn and performing as they should be.